<h1>About swissbib Basel Bern</h1>
<p>swissbib Basel Bern lists a total of more than 7 Mio. titles from over 200 <a href="<?= $this->basePath('Libraries') ?>" title="Liste der Institutionen">scientific libraries in Basel and Bern</a> among them libraries of the universities of Basel and Bern as well as universities of applied sciences and the Swiss National Library. In addition, the catalogue lists titles provided by the following institutions: Kooperative Speicherbibliothek, Zentralbibliothek Solothurn and the Swiss Federal Institute for Vocational Education and Training in Lausanne and Lugano.</p>
<p>The project is maintained by <a href="http://www.informationsverbund.ch/21.0.html" target="_blank">Verbund IDS Basel Bern</a> and relies on the infrastructure and know-how of the Swiss metacatalog <a href="https://www.swissbib.ch" target="_blank" title="swissbib">swissbib</a>.</p>
<h2>What does swissbib Basel Bern contain?</h2>
<p>swissbib Basel Bern contains two separate databases:</p>
<p><strong>Books & more</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>books/e-books, journals/e-journals, newspapers, CDs/DVDs, databases etc. Listed is the <strong>title information</strong> of those items, <strong>rather than articles or single chapters</strong>.</li>
    <li>Retro-digitised scientific journals from Switzerland (project E-Periodica), offering direct access to full text.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Articles & more</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>journal articles, chapters</strong> etc. from numerous e-journals, e-books and databases offered by the universities of Basel and Bern. From within the IP-range or VPN of the university articles are available as full text.</li>
    <li>freely available electronic resources from the internet, accessible without geographical restrictions.</li>
</ul>
<p>Titles without full text access can be ordered via <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i> SFX-Services at your library.</p>
